---
import Base from '@layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Terms of Service" description="Varax terms of service. License terms, acceptable use, and legal information.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-light-text mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-light-text-secondary mb-10">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing or using the Varax Labs website (varax.io) and related services, you agree to be
        bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, do not use our services.
      </p>

      <h2>Products and Licensing</h2>

      <h3>Onax (Free, Open Source)</h3>
      <p>
        Onax is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. You may use, modify, and
        distribute it in accordance with that license. The full license text is available in the
        project's GitHub repository.
      </p>

      <h3>Varax Compliance Platform</h3>
      <p>
        The Varax compliance platform free tier is available at no cost for non-commercial evaluation.
        The Pro tier requires a paid commercial license at the published subscription rate. License keys
        are non-transferable and are tied to your organization.
      </p>

      <h2>Payment Terms</h2>
      <p>
        Pro licenses are billed monthly or annually as selected at purchase. Payments are processed by
        Stripe. All prices are in USD. Subscriptions auto-renew unless cancelled before the renewal date.
      </p>

      <h3>Refund Policy</h3>
      <p>
        We offer a 30-day money-back guarantee on all Pro purchases. If you're not satisfied, contact
        <a href="mailto:support@varax.io">support@varax.io</a> within 30 days of purchase for a full refund.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Pro-tier components</li>
        <li>Share or redistribute Pro license keys</li>
        <li>Use the services for any unlawful purpose</li>
        <li>Attempt to disrupt or overload our website infrastructure</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        Our services are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied.
        Varax Labs does not warrant that the services will be uninterrupted, error-free, or that
        compliance reports will satisfy specific regulatory requirements without additional review.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, Varax Labs shall not be liable for any indirect,
        incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of our services. Our total
        liability shall not exceed the amount paid by you in the twelve months preceding the claim.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of the services after changes
        constitutes acceptance. Material changes will be communicated via email to registered users.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the United States. Any disputes shall be resolved
        in the courts of the state in which Varax Labs is incorporated.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@varax.io">hello@varax.io</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
